—ЩNarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/to_tsv.mdЩ@39c5c98f24eecc47561104fa380393c03e4c11298ffb0959ae1bd9b6af0a155a­title: to tsv‘ЁExamplesЪ›Outputs a TSV string representing the contents of this table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[foo bar]; [1 2]] | to tsv
foobar
12


```
Outputs a TSV string representing the contents of this record.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> {a: 1 b: 2} | to tsv
ab
12


```
Outputs a TSV stream with column names pre-determined.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[foo bar baz]; [1 2 3]] | to tsv --columns [baz foo]
bazfoo
31


```
